@startuml C4_Browsing_Domain

title C4 - Browsing Domain Model

top to bottom direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle bold
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

package "Domain" {
  enum IntegrityStatusEnum {
    VALID
    INVALID
    UNKNOWN
  }

  enum MetadataType {
    STRING
    NUMBER
    BOOLEAN
    COMPOSITE
  }

  class Dip <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +uuid: string
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class DocumentClass <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +dipId: number | null
    +dipUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +name: string
    +timestamp: string
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Process <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +documentClassId: number | null
    +documentClassUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +metadata: Metadata
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Document <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +processId: number | null
    +processUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +metadata: Metadata
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class File <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +documentId: number | null
    +documentUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +filename: string
    +path: string
    +hash: string
    +isMain: boolean
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Metadata <<value-object>> {
    +name: string
    +type: MetadataType
    +value: string | Metadata[]
  }
}

Dip "1" o-- "0..*" DocumentClass
DocumentClass "1" o-- "0..*" Process
Process "1" o-- "0..*" Document
Document "1" o-- "0..*" File

Process --> "1" Metadata : metadata
Document --> "1" Metadata : metadata
Metadata "1" o-- "0..*" Metadata : children

note right of Dip
Hierarchy used by browsing use cases:
Dip -> DocumentClass -> Process -> Document -> File
end note

note right of Process
This diagram reflects domain entities in core/src/entity.
Both id and parentUuid references are modeled because
they are used in domain flows and persistence mapping.
end note

@enduml
